http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/723-booths-set-up-in-Mandya-for-pulse-polio-drive/article14004292.ece

Deputy Commissioner M.N. Ajay Nagabhushan and district officer of the Indian Red Cross Society Meera Shivalingaiah on Sunday launched the annual pulse polio immunisation drive in Mandya district by administering anti-polio drops to a few children below the age of five.Mr. Nagabhushan and Ms. Shivalingaiah appealed to the people to cooperate with the officials to make the drive a success.The Department of Health and Family Welfare had established 723 booths across the district to administer the oral polio vaccine (OPV) to children, H.P. Manche Gowda, District Health Officer (DHO), said.The target was to cover 1,69,348 children during the first phase of the drive that began on Sunday.In the next three days, health workers and volunteers would visit houses in rural and urban areas to ensure that no child was left uncovered.A total of 2,892 health workers and 144 supervisors were roped in for the campaign.